Due to YouTube video length restrictions, this run was split into two videos:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q_fUT1Od9r8

For the sake of showing the continuous recording, the ten-second segment of 9:43:28 - 9:43:38 is shown in both halves.

So The D-Pad turned 8 in the days leading up to this stream, and I decided to hold a marathon stream of a quasi-blind run of Super Mario Sunshine.  For not having done any prep whatsoever and not going to maps or guides until we locked in the bottom spot on the leaderboard, 19:30 doesn't seem like the worst time in the world.

Definitely planning on coming back to it with an actual gameplan ahead of time somewhere down the road, but for now we welcome with open arms the losing slot on the board!

Note: I have a split labeled "120 Sprites" that should be "119 Sprites", and is treated as such in the run.  There is a separate "Bowser" split that comes after.

My friend Shane (guavaBageler) said he would give me $50 if I did a 120 shine run by the end of summer. This is that. I did get paid and got food. This all came up from me asking him to watch my Metroid: Zero Mission hundo speedruns and every time I said hundo he'd ask if it was Sunshine hundo and I would say no. This is like if a dumb joke combined with a hypothetical consumes a full day of your life and real money if on the line.
